defaultOnce a matter is in court, the more important the subject, the more difficult the issues, the more help we need to try and get the right answer. ... No particular formality is required and t
defaulthe invitation is a very open one, but not I think abused.
defaultCommenting that ‘provided they stick to the rules, interventions are enormously helpful’, she noted specifically that ‘[o]
defaultne
default thing that interveners can do, which the parties may find it more diffic
defaultult and more costly to do, is to draw our attention to international jurisprudence which may be relevant to the issue’.
