default&#xa0;defaultThe Public Sector Equality Dutydefault&#xa0;defaultImpact AssessmentdefaultEnsuring that the best interests of the child are a primary consideration in all actions concerning children (art. 3(1)), and t
defaulthat all the provisions of the Convention are respected in legislation and policy development and delivery at all levels of government demands a continuous process of child impact assessment (predicting the impact of any proposed law, policy or budgetary al
defaultlocation which affects children and the enjoyment of their rights) and child impact evaluation (evaluating the actual impact of implementation). This process needs to be built into government at all levels and as early as possible in the development of pol
defaulticy.
